## 2. Web Audio API — Key Patterns

### Sample-locked multistart
```js
const t = audioCtx.currentTime + 0.05;  // small scheduling offset
stems.forEach(s => s.source.start(t, pauseOffset % s.buffer.duration));
```

### Per-stem signal chain
```
AudioBufferSourceNode (loop=true)
  → GainNode (volume, 0–1)
  → StereoPannerNode (pan, -1 to +1)
  → GainNode (muteGain: 1 or 0)
  → masterGainNode
  → audioCtx.destination
```

### Pause/Resume
```js
// Pause: record offset, suspend context
pauseOffset += audioCtx.currentTime - playStartTime;
audioCtx.suspend();

// Resume: resume context, mark new playStartTime
audioCtx.resume();
playStartTime = audioCtx.currentTime;
```

### Seek (looped buffers)
```js
// Stop all sources, recalculate loop offset, restart
stems.forEach(s => { s.source.stop(); s.source.disconnect(); });
pauseOffset = seekSec;
// restart: source.start(t, seekSec % buffer.duration)
```

### Wilson Scheduler (Scheduler.js, ~50 lines)
```js
// Ref: https://web.dev/articles/audio-scheduling
const SCHEDULE_AHEAD = 0.1;   // 100ms lookahead
const TICK_INTERVAL = 25;     // 25ms setTimeout

class Scheduler {
  constructor(audioCtx, bpm, onBeat) { ... }
  start() { this._nextBeatTime = this.audioCtx.currentTime; this._tick(); }
  _tick() {
    while (this._nextBeatTime < this.audioCtx.currentTime + SCHEDULE_AHEAD) {
      this.onBeat(this._currentBeat, this._nextBeatTime);
      this._nextBeatTime += 60 / this.bpm;
      this._currentBeat++;
    }
    this._timerId = setTimeout(() => this._tick(), TICK_INTERVAL);
  }
  stop() { clearTimeout(this._timerId); }
}
// onBeat callback: fires cue card display via scheduler (timeSec match),
// drives metronome flash in Transport via postMessage or ref callback
```

### OfflineAudioContext stem generation
```js
async function renderStem(type, song, sampleRate = 44100) {
  const dur = song.loopDuration;  // barDuration * loopBars
  const offCtx = new OfflineAudioContext(2, Math.ceil(sampleRate * dur), sampleRate);
  // ... build oscillator graph on offCtx ...
  return offCtx.startRendering(); // returns Promise<AudioBuffer>
}
```

